- "average maximum temperature" is the mean of the maximum temperatures recorded for a city over the specified period;
- "overall average maximum temperature" is the mean of the maximum temperatures recorded across all cities for the specified period.

- 'crown of atmospheric stability' refers to the city with the highest average atmospheric pressure;
- 'high-quality weather recordings' refers to data with a data quality marked as 'high';
